    "narrative": "Our primary offensive anchors for today are **Will Smith** (73.95) and **Tyler Freeman** (71.80), both benefiting from significant park factors and favorable individual matchups. **Will Smith** draws a +14% park boost against Lorenzen, and his elite xwOBA metrics make him our most efficient play. Similarly, **Tyler Freeman** sees his projection elevated by an excellent matchup against Sasaki (5.52 xERA) and a neutral platoon advantage, allowing him to capitalize on a +19% SP skill bonus. While **Jonathan Aranda** (67.96) sits slightly behind them, he is a must-start today; the combination of a wind-out environment and a strong +12% platoon edge against right-hander Keller, M, positions him to outperform his base projection significantly.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Matt Chapman**, who fell just short of our starting threshold with a 52.85 score. While his +6% order bonus and +4% park factor are attractive, he was edged out by the superior platoon utility provided by **Luis Arraez** and **Gleyber Torres**, the latter of whom remains in our lineup despite the brutal matchup against Crochet (2.86 xERA) because of the sheer strength of his dynamic platoon advantage (+13%). We are closely monitoring the status of **Bryson Stott**; his 64.41 projection is contingent on the lineup assumption, as any drop in the batting order could deflate his value. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on the risks posed to **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez**, both of whom are facing the elite arm of Crochet. We have opted to bench **Drew Gilbert** entirely today, as his 39.46 score falls below our 40-point floor due to an unfavorable lefty-on-lefty matchup and a deep-order placement.",
